 continue to meet throughout the fourth class year  All cadets are urged to consult their advisers for assistance and advice at any time  The VMI Academic Advising Program provides opportunities for new cadets to visit with their advisers individually or in groups to discuss any academic  extra curricular or personal concerns  Cadets continue to consult the same adviser throughout the cadetship  unless a different degree program is selected  In addition  the Institute sponsors an Cadet Athlete Development Office to help scholar athletes keep their focus on academics  For information about advising  contact Major Simone McKelvey Associate Registrar for Advising Support  301 Shell Hall  To assist in the advising efforts  cadets and faculty advisers have real time access to individual academic information thru the administrative Post View web interface Click here to access Post View information and instructions  For an overview of VMI s FERPA rules and regulations click here  VMI FERPA Training VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu Virginia Military Institute   Advising Information  skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New Market Battlefield Stonewall Jackson House For Visitors Directions   Map Employment Parents   Family Conferences Chessi